6.	Explain auto, register, static and extern variables.
AUTO:
	Auto is the default storage class for all local variables
EX:
{	int variable;
        auto int variable1;
} 	

REGISTER:
	Register is used to define local variables with the same storage class auto can only
be used within functions(i.e)local variables
EX:
{
	register int variable;
}

STATIC:
	It is default storage class for gloabal bariables.The following two variables both have a sstatic
 storage class.
EX:
	static int variable;
	 int variable1;
   
EXTERN:
	Extern is used to give a refernce of a global variables that is visible to
all the program files.

